#photo";}i:134;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:0;}i:135;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:2;}i:136;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEubZdEJWM2";}i:137;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:250:"https://scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/p1080x1080/118702003_2614950195437293_3933232969991208558_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=101&_nc_ohc=r78zQ7QWbgwAX8KUnRT&oh=bf7e43d2a23b498f898796ce2dd629ef&oe=5F7ACD0D";}i:138;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:139;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:31489088013;}i:140;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:141;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:142;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:143;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2390968777855422929";}i:144;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEubW-BH1HR";}i:145;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599245724;}i:146;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:2210:"The word Jesus uses here for Anxiety is the Greek word 'Merimna'- and it means 'to care,' but in a distracting way. It comes from the root word 'Merizo,” which means “to divide or cut into pieces. 

Anxiety comes from things you care about that divide and cut your heart into a bunch of different pieces. Sound about right? 

Anxiety is care in the wrong direction. God made you care, the Devil twisted it into Anxiety. Anxiety is the counterfeit of care. 

So how do you begin to fight Anxiety back? 

Redirect your cares through Prayer. 

Phil 4:6 Do not be anxious about anything; INSTEAD pray about everything. Tell God what you need, and thank him for all he has done. 

Prayer is the exchange for Anxiety.

When I feel overwhelmed with anxiety, I stop what I’m doing, and go for a walk to pray. I vent my whole heart to God. I tell him the unfiltered version of how I feel. 

After I throw up all my emotions on to God, after a while I will notice I kind of hit a lull. I run out of things to say. That’s when I follow the next part of the verse above. I begin to thank him for what he has done. 

Telling God my needs gets the junk out. Thanking him puts the medication in. It recalibrates our hearts. 

I find anything and everything to thank him. 

Phil 4: 7 Then you will experience God’s peace, which exceeds anything we can understand. His peace will guard your hearts and minds as you live in Christ Jesus.

After I thank him for a while, the strangest thing starts to happen. I start to feel a quieting in my spirit and emotions. Like the verse promises, “you will experience a peace that surpasses understanding.” I don’t know why, but I just start to feel peace again."

Excerpt from my post "The Truth about Anxiety. How to Overcome with 4 Biblical Tips." Check out the full post in my bio, and subscribe! 
